nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.formalisms.flow

Class Seize<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,R extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<R>,T extends SimTime<A,R,T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventProducer
      • nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.formalisms.flow.Station<A,R,T>
        • nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.formalisms.flow.Seize<A,R,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - the absolute storage type for the simulation time, e.g. Calendar, Duration, or Double.
    R - the relative type for time storage, e.g. Long for the Calendar. For most non-calendar types, the absolute and relative types are the same.
    T - the extended type itself to be able to implement a comparator on the simulation time.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, StationInterface, ResourceRequestorInterface<A,R,T>, nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventProducerInterface
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Seize.CalendarDouble, Seize.CalendarFloat, Seize.CalendarLong, Seize.TimeDouble, Seize.TimeDoubleUnit, Seize.TimeFloat, Seize.TimeFloatUnit, Seize.TimeLong

    public class Seize<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,R extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<R>,T extends SimTime<A,R,T>>
extends Station<A,R,T>
implements ResourceRequestorInterface<A,R,T>
    The Seize requests a resource and releases an entity whenever this resource is actually claimed.
